ption is non-functional without unlock flow.\",\n    \"URGENT: Remove course code hardcoding. Move `BABS1201`, `BABS1202`, `ARTS5200` to database or config. Breaks Blueprint rule 3 (Universal Architecture).\",\n    \"URGENT: Require CSRF token (or SameSite cookies) for all state changes. Add token to forms and validate on all mutations.\",\n    \"Remove `?reset=true` query parameter or require multi-step confirmation. Prevent accidental/malicious localStorage wipe.\",\n    \"Wrap passphrase unlock in visible UI flow (modal, settings page, first-launch dialog). Call `unlockWithPassphrase()` on app mount or user action.\",\n    \"Add input validation to `fetchLMSData(courseCode)`. Whitelist valid codes or reject invalid input with clear error.\",\n    \"Implement proper error propagation: throw on appendEvent fail instead of silent console.warn. Let caller decide on retry/fallback.\",\n    \"Persist queued events when vault is locked, don't silently drop. Resume sync when unlocked. Or surface warning to user.\",\n    \"Add rate limiting: debounce focus session calls, cap event submissions to 100/min per session.\",\n    \"Encrypt localStorage at rest. Current plaintext salt + stored state is visible in DevTools. Consider using a service worker + IndexedDB with encryption.\",\n    \"Add CORS headers if serving from different origin. CSP headers to block inline scripts.\",\n    \"Document the intended authentication model in CLAUDE.md. Current code has no clear security model.\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Critical Issues**\n\n**Risk Score: 68/100** — Multiple high-severity gaps.\n\n### Why This Score\n\n1. **No authentication** — Anyone can access the dashboard. Multi-tenant isolation is completely absent.\n2. **Encryption never unlocked** — The HistoryOfThought passphrase system is dead code; no UI calls `unlockWithPassphrase()`.\n3. **Query param bypass** — `?reset=true` silently wipes localStorage without consent.\n4. **Multi-tenant violation** — Course codes hardcoded in logic break the \"Universal Architecture\" rule in your CLAUDE.md.\n5. **Silent failures** — Errors vanish into console, hiding real problems from users.\n\n### What to Fix First\n\n1. Wire up the passphrase unlock UI (settings modal, first-launch flow).\n2. Add authentication (even basic session-based is better than none).\n3. Remove the hardcoded course codes and move them to a config/database.\n4. Require CSRF tokens on all state mutations.\n\nThe codebase is well-structured and React's auto-escaping prevents obvious XSS, but **the absence of auth + the defunct encryption are load-bearing vulnerabilities** that need immediate attention before production use.\n",
